{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Starting MapLibre iOS 6.10.0, using "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.protomaps.com\/pmtiles\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a data source is supported. You can prefix your vector tile source with "},{"code":"pmtiles:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a PMTiles file. The rest of the URL continue with be "},{"code":"https:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a remote PMTiles file, "},{"code":"asset:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to load an asset or "},{"code":"file:\/\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a local PMTiles file."}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"PMTiles sources currently do not support caching or offline pack downloads."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Oliver Wipfli has made a style available that combines a "},{"identifier":"","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" basemap togehter with Foursquare’s POI dataset. It is available in the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" repository on GitHub. The style to use is"}]},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles\/refs\/heads\/main\/style.json"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The neat thing about this style is that it only uses PMTiles vector sources. PMTiles can be hosted with a relatively simple file server (or file hosting service) instead of a more complex specialized tile server.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"pmtiles-demo.png","type":"image"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Working with PMTiles","type":"text"}],"seeA